# S07-T6: Logic-Perfect — Task Detail Edit and Delete
# S07-T6-LogicTaskDetailEditDelete.pd

**Objective:** Implement task detail panel behavior in totem-view to match taskboard-supabase: edit title/description/status (and persist), delete task (with confirmation if present in reference), close panel on delete, and success/error toasts.

**Context:**
- Reference: `taskboard-supabase/client/src/components/modules/taskDetails/TaskDetails.vue` (edit mode, update, delete), `composables/useTaskOperations.ts` (update, remove), useNotification/toasts. Panel closes when selected task is deleted; list/board view updates.

**Gate:** OPEN

**requires:** [BUILD]

**Steps:**
1. In task detail panel: editable title/description/status (inline or edit mode) per reference; on save call update handler (API or state).
2. Delete action: if reference has confirmation (e.g. TaskDeleteConfirmation), implement same; on confirm call remove handler; close detail panel and clear selected task; refresh board task list.
3. Wire toasts for update/delete success and errors to match reference (message text and type).
4. Ensure closing panel (backdrop, close button) clears selection and matches reference behavior.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- User can edit task in detail panel and delete task (with same confirmation flow as reference). Panel closes on delete; list updates; toasts match. Logic parity with taskboard-supabase.
